cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.DC, cs.NI

This paper deals with the control of a dynamic system using multiple sensor-actuator agents, which suggests that it falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of state estimation and event-triggering protocols also indicates that it could belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The application of the approach to the control of a vehicle platoon suggests that it could also be classified under robotics (cs.RO) or distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of a common bus network for data exchange implies that it could belong to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
